as governor there a Turkish commander, Čaḡri or Jaʿfar. In summer of 617/1220 the Mongols first appeared at Balḵ.]&lt;/ref>&lt;br />[[Sultanate of Rum]] (&lt;small>[[Malatya]]: 1217–1219; [[Akşehir]]: 1219–1222; [[Karaman|Larende]]: 1222–1228; [[Konya]]: 1228–1273&lt;/small>)&lt;ref name=\"encyclopaedia1991\" />"},"religion":{"wt":"[[Islam]]"},"denomination":{"wt":"[[Sunni]]&lt;ref>{{cite|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1y-hxhLSWsEC&amp;pg=PA48|title=The Complete Idiot&apos;s Guide to Rumi Meditations|page=48|publisher=Penguin Group|}}&lt;/ref>"},"jurisprudence":{"wt":"[[Hanafi]]"},"Sufi_order":{"wt":"[[Mevlevi]]"},"main_interests":{"wt":"[[Sufi poetry]], [[Hanafi]] jurisprudence"},"notable_ideas":{"wt":"[[Sufi whirling]], [[Muraqaba]]"},"works":{"wt":"[[Masnavi|&apos;&apos;Mathnawī-ī ma&apos;nawī&apos;&apos;]], [[Diwan-e Shams-e Tabrizi|&apos;&apos;Dīwān-ī Shams-ī Tabrīzī&apos;&apos;]], [[Fihi Ma Fihi|&apos;&apos;Fīhi mā fīhi&apos;&apos;]]\n&lt;!--|predecessor = [[Baha-ud-din Zakariya]] and [[Shams Tabraiz]]-->"},"influences":{"wt":"[[Muhammad]], [[Al-Ghazali]], [[Muhaqqeq Termezi]], [[Baha-ud-din Zakariya]], [[Farid al-Din Attar|Attār]], [[Sanai|Sanā&apos;ī]], [[Abusaeid Abolkheir|Abu Sa&apos;īd Abulḫayr]], [[Abul-Hassan Kharaqani|Ḫaraqānī]], [[Bayazid Bistami|Bayazīd Bistāmī]], [[Sultan Walad]], [[Shams Tabriz|Šamse Tabrīzī]]"},"influenced":{"wt":"[[Jami]], [[Shah Abdul Latif Bhittai]], [[Kazi Nazrul Islam]], [[Abdolhossein Zarrinkoob]], [[Abdolkarim Soroush]], [[Hossein Elahi Ghomshei]], [[Muhammad Iqbal]]"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwCg"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background:
