<li><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Ehsan_Yarshater" title="Ehsan Yarshater">Ehsan Yarshater</a></li></ul>
</div></td></tr></tbody></table><div></div></td></tr></tbody></table><div></div></td></tr><tr><td class="navbox-abovebelow" colspan="2"><div>Contemporary Persian and Classical Persian are the same language, but writers since 1900 are classified as contemporary. At one time, Persian was a common cultural language of much of the non-Arabic Islamic world.  Today it is the official language of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a>, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Tajikistan" title="Tajikistan">Tajikistan</a> and one of the two official languages of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a>.</div></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
